The paper deals with the problem of clustering a point set with limited distance information, which is a fundamental problem in data science and machine learning. The use of landmarks and active selection strategy suggests that the paper may belong to the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques to cluster proteins, which suggests that it may belong to the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of distance queries and clustering algorithms suggests that it may belong to the category of databases (cs.DB) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper involves empirical studies and evaluation of the proposed algorithm, which suggests that it may belong to the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
